subject: Golf
lead_paragraph: Oliver Wilson of England shot a five-under-par 67 and led by one stroke after three rounds of the South African Open. Wilson was at four-under 212 heading into the final round, with the halfway leader, James Kingston, in second place. Garth Mulroy was two shots back after a 64, the day’s best round. Greg Norman shot a 72 and was at 217. The defending champion, Ernie Els, was at 224.
